cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using a theorem prover to conduct formal verification of Fault Tree Analysis, which involves logical reasoning. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a complementary approach to traditional FTA-based analyses, which is relevant to software engineering practices. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper involves formalizing generic Fault Tree gates and verifying their failure probability expressions, which can be seen as a programming language task. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper involves probabilistic reasoning, which is a common topic in AI research. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper focuses on safety-critical systems and their dependability analysis, which is relevant to systems and control research.
